-- Tom Brady Has Three Touchdowns as Patriots Defeat Tim Tebow’s Broncos
-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 2011-12-19T00:30:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-19/tom-brady-has-three-touchdowns-as-patriots-defeat-tim-tebow-s-broncos.html
Tom Brady  threw two touchdown passes
and ran for a third score as the New England Patriots defeated
 Tim Tebow ’s Broncos 41-23 today in Denver.  Brady threw for 320 yards as the Patriots improved to an
American Football Conference-best 11-3. Tebow ran for two scores
for the AFC West-leading Broncos (8-6), who had a six-game
winning streak snapped.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
